[SN]TITLE[SN]
Geraint Thomas: Lead in Tour of the Alps cut with stage remaining

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Welsh cyclist Geraint Thomas' lead at the front of the Tour of the Alps has been cut to 13 seconds with just one stage remaining.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Italy's Matteo Montaguti beat France's Thibaut Pinot to claim a narrow victory in the fourth stage on Thursday.
Pinot had led going into the final 50 metres of the stage, but Montaguti over took him just before the finish line.
Team Sky's Thomas finished with the peloton to retain his race lead going into the final stage.
